This paper discusses the development of a fully-fledged index for grammar-compressed trees, which is used to execute arbitrary tree algorithms with a slow-down that is comparable to the space improvement. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures (cs.DS), digital libraries (cs.DL), and software engineering (cs.SE).
